
<p>After you upload your video to YouTube or Vimeo, you can add your video to a post on WordPress so that the featured image of the post (and the thumbnail on the homepage) will be the video itself.</p>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-6">
    <iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/74733433" width="100%" height="400" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-6">
    <p>PUT IT INTO PRACTICE:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Create your post
      </li>
      <li>
        Put the video ID (not the entire URL) in the box on the edit page for the post.
      </li>
      <li>
        Select “player” for the “Type of Video Thumb”.
      </li>  
      <li>
        Change the type of post to “Video”.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>

